Police Minister Bheki Cele and Home Affairs Minister Aaron Motsoaledi addressed community members in Diepsloot following a meeting residents. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A high level delegation including Police Minister Bheki Cele, Home Affairs Minister Aaron Motsoaledi and Gauteng Premier David Makhura have spent Friday morning assessing security in Diepsloot. The police have released a statement disputing the number of people murdered since 30 March. READ:Â Murdered Zimbabwean's wife flees her home They claim the Diepsloot Police Station has record of five reported murders, this is in contradiction of the seven mentioned by Premier David Makhura and numerous community members. There are also reports of discrimination where people are being asked for documentation The Diepsloot Community Policing Forum says a long-term sustainable solution is needed to fight crime in the area. South Africans are being urged not to take the law into their own hands. Home Affairs Minister Aaron Motsoaledi and Gauteng Premier, David Makhura are in Diepsloot. They are the latest to condemn the attacks on foreign nationals there. #eNCA's Pule Letshwiti-Jones has more details. Courtesy #DStv403